categories.summary: The customer expresses that imurica EMEA looks better than Spotler, finding Spotler clunky and requiring frequent support tickets. They also appreciate that imurica EMEA's analytics already include engagement rate percentage, which Spotler requires manual calculation for. The customer also states that Meltwater alongside Spotler would have been more expensive than imurica EMEA, and they like the idea of having everything in one platform.

The customer asks if Brandwatch is imurica EMEA's equivalent of Buzz Zummo. The seller responds by stating that Brandwatch is very much like Hootsuite and Buzz Zummo, serving as a social listening and engagement platform.

The customer inquired about the platform's ability to delete, hide, and block users during a potential crisis, expressing uncertainty about whether these actions could be performed within the platform or if they would need to go through Meta/Facebook directly. The customer also asked if the platform has the ability to pull results with a certain tag attached to it.
The customer mentioned needing to check with their budget, indicating a potential concern about the cost of the solution.
The customer experienced a system outage during the call, which could raise concerns about the reliability and stability of the platform.

The customer mentions that her line manager will have the overall say as to whether they can go ahead with the platform. The sales rep also inquires whether the decision could be signed off this month to apply an incentive.

Samantha mentions that Katherine and James's input is important, indicating they are stakeholders in the decision. She also mentions a new Leeds person whose opinion will be considered. Rhiannon will discuss with Katherine and James later. Rhiannon mentions she needs to speak to Spotler to see how things are left.

Rhiannon mentions that they are coming to the end of the invoice period with Spotler, suggesting a potential timeline for switching. The sales rep mentions an incentive that is only available for this month. Rhiannon hopes the decision will be made by the end of the week.

summary.text: This sales meeting between Sarah (representing a social media platform with integrated PR and marketing tools) and Samantha, James, and Katherine (potential buyers) involved a deep dive into the platform's capabilities. Isabella demonstrated social media scheduling, engagement tracking, crisis communication features, and in-depth analytics, highlighting the integration of Brandwatch for historical data and AI-driven content suggestions. The buyers, particularly James and Katherine, inquired about specific functionalities like comment deletion, tagging capabilities, customized reporting, and competitive benchmarking. Samantha expressed satisfaction with the platform, noting it as a potentially cost-effective, all-in-one solution compared to their current setup (Spotler) and alternatives like Meltwater. She requested a report on positive sentiment related to "Eastbourne" for internal pitching purposes, and inquired about support hours for new staff training. Isabella committed to providing the report and further answering questions via a shared portal, also emphasizing a limited-time discount incentive. The buyers aim to make a decision quickly, potentially this month.
